      "message": "Since this isn’t actually always on a background thread anymore (it’s not in this call), let’s rename it to be more about what it does and less about where it does it. StartHandlerProcess()?\n\nOr leave BackgroundHandlerStartThreadProc() if you like to see thread entry points like that, but transfer all of the guts to a new function, to get rid of the WINAPI and int-instead-of-bool thing where it’s not required by the OS’ interface. And then we can go back to making the WINAPI version do the thing that’s more natural for it, where success would be 0.",
